      • writeGraphsFromDS2

        public static void writeGraphsFromDS2​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​org.jgrapht.Graph<MyVertex,​org.jgrapht.graph.DefaultWeightedEdge>> graphs)
                               throws java.io.IOException,
                                      org.jgrapht.io.ExportException,
                                      java.net.URISyntaxException,
                                      javax.xml.transform.TransformerException
        Takes the result of createGraphsFromDS2(IterableResult) and, for each graph, serializes and writes it in a DOT file, then takes the serialized graph and uses it to produce a plot. By default, the plot is created using GraphUtils.writeImage(File, String, String), but, if the graph is too big for GraphViz, it falls back on GraphUtils.writeImage(Graph, String, String).
        Parameters:
        graphs - The Map returned by createGraphsFromDS2(IterableResult).
        Throws:
        org.jgrapht.io.ExportException - rethrown if raised by GraphUtils.saveDS2Graph(Graph, String).
        java.io.IOException - rethrown if raised by GraphUtils.saveDS2Graph(Graph, String) or GraphUtils.writeImage(File, String, String).
        java.net.URISyntaxException - rethrown if raised by GraphUtils.saveDS2Graph(Graph, String) or GraphUtils.writeImage(File, String, String) or GraphUtils.writeImage(Graph, String, String).
        javax.xml.transform.TransformerException - rethrown if raised by GraphUtils.writeImage(Graph, String, String).
